x4freetext: Enriched 111Cd target (> 0.99
enrichment) with a thickness of 159 +/- 6 ug/cm2
Q3D magnetic spectrograph with a position
sensitive cathode strip detector
The experiment used polarized deuteron
beam (80 % polarization). Proton spectra were recorded
in two settings of the Q3D spectrometer:
1. ground state and to 2.4 MeV excitation energy
2. 2-4.2 MeV excitation energy range
Transfer data were collected for angles 10-50 degrees
in steps of 5 degrees. Additional data at 60 degrees
were taken in the second setting of the spectrometer.
Elastic scattering data were collected for 15-115
degrees for target thickness determination and optical
potential analysis.
reported uncertainty, which includes the
following systematic components:
Uncertainty associated with dead time and
beam current integration (approx. 1%)
Normalization of the transfer cross section
MPT
